  "title": "Talking About Money and Asking for Prices in Egyptian Arabic",
  "dialect": "egyptian-arabic",
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Introduction to Money Vocabulary",
          "arabic": "مقدمة لمفردات الفلوس"
        },
        "text": "Let's start by learning some basic words related to money in Egyptian Arabic. The most common word for 'money' in general is فلوس (filoos).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "فلوس",
            "english": "Money",
            "transliteration": "filoos"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "The Egyptian Pound: 'Geneih'",
          "arabic": "الجنيه المصري: «جنيه»"
        },
        "text": "The official currency of Egypt is the Egyptian Pound. In Egyptian Arabic, it's called جنيه.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "جنيه",
            "english": "Egyptian Pound",
            "transliteration": "geneih"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "واحد جنيه",
            "english": "One pound",
            "transliteration": "waaḥed geneih"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "عشرة جنيهات",
            "english": "Ten pounds",
            "transliteration": "ʿashara geneihaat"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Fractions of a Pound: 'Ersh'",
          "arabic": "أجزاء الجنيه: «قرش»"
        },
        "text": "One Egyptian Pound is divided into 100 piasters. A piaster is called قرش. While often used in smaller denominations, you might still hear it, especially for exact prices.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "قرش",
            "english": "Piaster",
            "transliteration": "ersh"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "خمسين قرش",
            "english": "Fifty piasters (half a pound)",
            "transliteration": "khamsīn ersh"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
