    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'How much?' for a singular item",
          "arabic": "كيف تسأل «بكام؟» لشيء مفرد"
        },
        "text": "To ask 'How much?' for a single item, use the phrase بكام ده؟ (bi-kam da?) for masculine items, or بكام دي؟ (bi-kam di?) for feminine items. Remember that 'ده' and 'دي' mean 'this'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "بكام ده؟",
            "english": "How much is this? (masc.)",
            "transliteration": "bi-kam da?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "بكام دي؟",
            "english": "How much is this? (fem.)",
            "transliteration": "bi-kam di?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'How much?' for plural items",
          "arabic": "كيف تسأل «بكام؟» لأشياء جمع"
        },
        "text": "When asking about the price of multiple items, use بكام دول؟ (bi-kam dool?). 'دول' means 'these' (plural).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "بكام دول؟",
            "english": "How much are these?",
            "transliteration": "bi-kam dool?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "The word for 'price'",
          "arabic": "كلمة «سعر» أو «تمن» (ثمن)"
        },
        "text": "The word for 'price' is سعر (saʿr) or تمن (taman). You can use it in a sentence like 'what is its price?'",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "كام سعره؟",
            "english": "How much is its price? (masc.)",
            "transliteration": "kam saʿroh?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "كام تمنها؟",
            "english": "How much is its price? (fem.)",
            "transliteration": "kam tamanha?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
