    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking for a Discount: 'Khasm'",
          "arabic": "طلب خصم: «خصم»"
        },
        "text": "Bargaining is common in many markets in Egypt. You can ask for a 'discount' using the word خصم. A common phrase is 'ممكن تعملي خصم؟' (Momken taʿameli khasm?) for a female seller or 'ممكن تعمل خصم؟' (Momken taʿmel khasm?) for a male seller, meaning 'Can you make a discount?'",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "خصم",
            "english": "Discount",
            "transliteration": "khasm"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "ممكن تعمل خصم؟",
            "english": "Can you make a discount? (to male)",
            "transliteration": "momken taʿmel khasm?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking to Lower the Price: 'Tanzīl'",
          "arabic": "طلب تخفيض السعر: «تنزيل»"
        },
        "text": "Another way to ask for a lower price is to use phrases like 'ممكن تنزل شوية؟' (Momken tenazzal shwaya?) meaning 'Can you lower it a little?' or 'قلل السعر شوية' (qallil es-saʿr shwaya) meaning 'Lower the price a little'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "ممكن تنزل شوية؟",
            "english": "Can you lower it a little?",
            "transliteration": "momken tenazzal shwaya?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Polite Bargaining Phrases",
          "arabic": "عبارات المساومة المهذبة"
        },
        "text": "To be polite while bargaining, you can add 'لو سمحت' (law samaḥt) meaning 'please' (to a male) or 'لو سمحتي' (law samaḥti) (to a female).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "ده سعره غالي، ممكن تعمل خصم لو سمحت؟",
